50|$|The two Command Based Post Offices at Delhi and Kolkota and Army Postal Service Centre at Kamptee Nagpur are {{commanded}} by Commandants in {{the rank of}} Colonel. The Officers Commanding Corps/Divisional/Area/Border Roads/Assam Rifles/Air Force Postal Units in the rank of Lt Col/ Major/Captain monitor the functioning of Field Post Offices under their control and discharge {{the functions of the}} Postal Advisor to the <b>General-Officer-Commanding.</b> Two Central Base Post Offices and Section Base Post Offices serve as the nodal points for mail processing.|$|E
